---
import WellnessLayout from '../../../../layouts/WellnessLayout.astro';
---

<WellnessLayout title="Hormone Optimization — Lumen Health House" description="Comprehensive hormone panel, clinical interpretation, and personalized optimization plan with ongoing provider guidance.">

<!-- ═══ Hero — dark, left-aligned ═══ -->
<section class="wh-section wh-section--dark sp-hero">
	<div class="wh-container">
		<p class="wh-eyebrow">Hormones & Vitality</p>
		<h1>Hormone Optimization</h1>
		<p class="sp-hero__headline">Comprehensive hormone assessment and personalized protocols — guided by your labs, not guesswork.</p>
		<p class="wh-lead">In-depth hormone panels, clinical interpretation beyond generic reference ranges, and ongoing provider guidance for fatigue, mood, libido, and metabolic support. Consultation and labs required.</p>
		<div class="wh-btn-row">
			<a class="wh-btn wh-btn--primary" href="/demos/premium-wellness-clinic/new-clients">Book a Consultation &rarr;</a>
			<a class="wh-btn wh-btn--secondary" href="/demos/premium-wellness-clinic/memberships">View Memberships</a>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="wh-container sp-facts">
		<div class="sp-facts__strip">
			<div class="sp-facts__item"><span class="sp-facts__label">Duration</span><span class="sp-facts__value">45–60 min initial</span></div>
			<div class="sp-facts__item"><span class="sp-facts__label">Best for</span><span class="sp-facts__value">Fatigue, mood, libido, metabolism</span></div>
			<div class="sp-facts__item"><span class="sp-facts__label">Consultation</span><span class="sp-facts__value">Required</span></div>
			<div class="sp-facts__item"><span class="sp-facts__label">Starting at</span><span class="sp-facts__value">$350</span></div>
			<div class="sp-facts__item"><span class="sp-facts__label">Recommended</span><span class="sp-facts__value">Quarterly labs + follow-ups</span></div>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<!-- ═══ Why People Book — default bg, numbered list ═══ -->
<section class="wh-section sp-benefits">
	<div class="wh-container">
		<div class="wh-section-header">
			<p class="wh-eyebrow">Benefits</p>
			<h2>Why people choose hormone optimization</h2>
		</div>
		<div class="sp-benefits__list">
			<div class="sp-benefits__item">
				<span class="sp-benefits__num">01</span>
				<div>
					<h3>Comprehensive hormone panel</h3>
					<p>Testing goes beyond basic screenings — we assess a full range of hormones, binding proteins, and metabolic markers for a complete picture.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="sp-benefits__item">
				<span class="sp-benefits__num">02</span>
				<div>
					<h3>Provider interpretation</h3>
					<p>Your results are reviewed by a licensed provider who interprets them in context — not against generic lab ranges, but relative to your symptoms and goals.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="sp-benefits__item">
				<span class="sp-benefits__num">03</span>
				<div>
					<h3>Personalized protocol</h3>
					<p>Every plan is built around your unique hormonal profile, lifestyle, and health objectives — never a one-size-fits-all template.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="sp-benefits__item">
				<span class="sp-benefits__num">04</span>
				<div>
					<h3>Ongoing monitoring</h3>
					<p>Quarterly labs and regular follow-ups ensure your protocol stays dialed in as your body responds and your goals evolve.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="sp-benefits__item">
				<span class="sp-benefits__num">05</span>
				<div>
					<h3>Fatigue, mood, and libido support</h3>
					<p>Address the root causes of low energy, irritability, brain fog, low drive, and emotional flatness through targeted hormone balancing.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="sp-benefits__item">
				<span class="sp-benefits__num">06</span>
				<div>
					<h3>Metabolic support</h3>
					<p>Hormonal imbalances often contribute to weight gain resistance, poor body composition, and sluggish metabolism — optimizing hormones can help.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<!-- ═══ What It Is — default bg, editorial prose ═══ -->
<section class="wh-section sp-what">
	<div class="wh-container sp-what__inner">
		<h2>What is hormone optimization?</h2>
		<p>Hormone optimization is a clinical approach to identifying and addressing hormonal imbalances that affect energy, mood, body composition, libido, cognition, and overall vitality. Rather than waiting for levels to reach "clinically deficient" thresholds, optimization focuses on restoring hormones to ranges where you feel and function your best.</p>
		<p>At Lumen Health House, the process begins with a comprehensive hormone panel and an in-depth consultation with your provider. Together, you'll review results in the context of your symptoms, health history, and goals — then build a personalized plan that may include lifestyle interventions, nutraceuticals, or prescription-based therapies where medically appropriate.</p>
		<p>This is not a quick fix. Hormone optimization is an ongoing clinical relationship with regular lab monitoring, protocol adjustments, and transparent communication between you and your provider at every step.</p>
	</div>
</section>

<!-- ═══ Lab Review Pathway — surface bg, vertical timeline ═══ -->
<section class="wh-section wh-section--surface sp-labpath">
	<div class="wh-container">
		<div class="wh-section-header">
			<p class="wh-eyebrow">Your Optimization Path</p>
			<h2>From symptoms to a provider-guided plan.</h2>
		</div>
		<div class="sp-labpath__timeline">
			<div class="sp-labpath__step">
				<div class="sp-labpath__marker">
					<span class="sp-labpath__num">01</span>
					<span class="sp-labpath__dot"></span>
				</div>
				<div class="sp-labpath__body">
					<h3>Symptoms &amp; Goals</h3>
					<p>Discuss what you're experiencing — fatigue, mood changes, low drive, metabolic shifts</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="sp-labpath__step">
				<div class="sp-labpath__marker">
					<span class="sp-labpath__num">02</span>
					<span class="sp-labpath__dot"></span>
				</div>
				<div class="sp-labpath__body">
					<h3>Comprehensive Labs</h3>
					<p>Full hormone panel: testosterone, estrogen, thyroid, cortisol, DHEA, and metabolic markers</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="sp-labpath__step">
				<div class="sp-labpath__marker">
					<span class="sp-labpath__num">03</span>
					<span class="sp-labpath__dot"></span>
				</div>
				<div class="sp-labpath__body">
					<h3>Provider Review</h3>
					<p>Detailed clinical interpretation of your results in context of your history and goals</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="sp-labpath__step">
				<div class="sp-labpath__marker">
					<span class="sp-labpath__num">04</span>
					<span class="sp-labpath__dot"></span>
				</div>
				<div class="sp-labpath__body">
					<h3>Protocol Options</h3>
					<p>If appropriate, your provider discusses optimization approaches — bioidentical, peptide, or lifestyle-first</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="sp-labpath__step">
				<div class="sp-labpath__marker">
					<span class="sp-labpath__num">05</span>
					<span class="sp-labpath__dot"></span>
				</div>
				<div class="sp-labpath__body">
					<h3>Monitoring</h3>
					<p>Follow-up labs at 90 days, ongoing adjustments, and regular provider check-ins</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
		<p class="sp-labpath__note"><em>Hormone optimization requires clinical eligibility. Not all clients are candidates for hormone therapy. Your provider will only recommend a protocol if supported by labs, symptoms, and health history.</em></p>
	</div>
</section>

<!-- ═══ Who It's For — surface bg, two-column ═══ -->
<section class="wh-section wh-section--surface sp-who">
	<div class="wh-container sp-who__split">
		<h2>Who is hormone optimization for?</h2>
		<div class="sp-who__col">
			<h3>Goal-based</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>Restore energy, drive, and mental sharpness</li>
				<li>Support healthy body composition and metabolism</li>
				<li>Improve libido and sexual wellness</li>
				<li>Optimize performance and recovery</li>
				<li>Age proactively with provider guidance</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
		<div class="sp-who__col">
			<h3>Symptom-based</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>Persistent fatigue despite adequate sleep and nutrition</li>
				<li>Unexplained weight gain or loss resistance</li>
				<li>Low libido or sexual dysfunction</li>
				<li>Mood changes, irritability, or brain fog</li>
				<li>Muscle loss or slow recovery from exercise</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<!-- ═══ How It Works — dark bg, vertical timeline ═══ -->
<section class="wh-section wh-section--dark sp-process">
	<div class="wh-container">
		<div class="wh-section-header">
			<p class="wh-eyebrow">The Process</p>
			<h2>How hormone optimization works</h2>
		</div>
		<ol class="sp-process__steps">
			<li class="sp-process__step">
				<div class="sp-process__dot" aria-hidden="true"></div>
				<div class="sp-process__body"><h3>Consultation</h3><p>Meet with your provider to review symptoms, health history, goals, and determine eligibility for testing.</p></div>
			</li>
			<li class="sp-process__step">
				<div class="sp-process__dot" aria-hidden="true"></div>
				<div class="sp-process__body"><h3>Comprehensive labs</h3><p>A full hormone panel is drawn — including testosterone, estrogen, thyroid, DHEA, cortisol, and metabolic markers.</p></div>
			</li>
			<li class="sp-process__step">
				<div class="sp-process__dot" aria-hidden="true"></div>
				<div class="sp-process__body"><h3>Results & protocol</h3><p>Your provider interprets results in context, explains findings, and presents a personalized optimization plan.</p></div>
			</li>
			<li class="sp-process__step">
				<div class="sp-process__dot" aria-hidden="true"></div>
				<div class="sp-process__body"><h3>Monitor & adjust</h3><p>Quarterly labs and follow-up visits ensure your protocol remains effective and your levels stay optimized.</p></div>
			</li>
		</ol>
	</div>
</section>

<!-- ═══ What to Expect — default bg, simple sections ═══ -->
<section class="wh-section sp-expect">
	<div class="wh-container">
		<h2>What to expect</h2>
		<div class="sp-expect__phases">
			<div class="sp-expect__phase">
				<h3>Before</h3>
				<p>Complete your intake forms and health questionnaire. Fasting may be required for certain lab panels — your team will provide specific instructions before your visit.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="sp-expect__phase">
				<h3>During</h3>
				<p>Your initial visit includes a blood draw for comprehensive hormone testing and a 45–60 minute provider consultation to discuss your symptoms, history, and goals.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="sp-expect__phase">
				<h3>After</h3>
				<p>Results are typically available within 5–7 days. A follow-up visit reviews findings and launches your personalized protocol. You'll have ongoing access to your provider for questions.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<!-- ═══ Safety — sage bg, editorial ═══ -->
<section class="wh-section wh-section--sage sp-safety">
	<div class="wh-container sp-safety__inner">
		<h2>Safety, eligibility, and important disclosures</h2>
		<p><strong>A consultation and lab work are required before any hormone optimization protocol is initiated.</strong> Prescription-based services require medical eligibility determined through clinical assessment.</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Eligibility may depend on your health history, medications, lab results, and provider review.</li>
			<li>Hormone therapy (including testosterone, peptides, and other prescription protocols) is only prescribed when clinically appropriate and safe for the individual.</li>
			<li>Not all clients will qualify for prescription-based interventions. Your provider will discuss all available options transparently.</li>
			<li>Results vary by individual. Hormone optimization is a process — changes typically develop over weeks to months, not days.</li>
			<li>Ongoing lab monitoring is required for all prescription-based hormone protocols to ensure safety and efficacy.</li>
			<li>This service is not intended to diagnose, treat, or cure any disease. It is a clinical wellness service provided under licensed provider supervision.</li>
		</ul>
		<p style="margin-top:1.25rem; font-size:0.82rem; color:var(--wh-muted);"><em>Disclaimer: Individual results vary. Prescription-based services require medical eligibility. No specific outcome is promised or guaranteed. Hormone optimization is not appropriate for all individuals.</em></p>
	</div>
</section>

<!-- ═══ Packages — default bg, bordered cards ═══ -->
<section class="wh-section sp-packages">
	<div class="wh-container">
		<div class="wh-section-header">
			<p class="wh-eyebrow">Program Pricing</p>
			<h2>Investment in your vitality</h2>
		</div>
		<div class="sp-packages__grid">
			<div class="wh-card sp-packages__card">
				<h3>Initial Assessment</h3>
				<p class="sp-packages__price">From $350</p>
				<p>Provider consultation, comprehensive hormone panel, and personalized protocol development.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="wh-card sp-packages__card">
				<h3>Quarterly Follow-Up</h3>
				<p class="sp-packages__price">$225/visit</p>
				<p>Lab recheck, provider review, and protocol adjustment as needed.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="wh-card sp-packages__card">
				<h3>Vitality Membership</h3>
				<p class="sp-packages__price">$425/mo</p>
				<p>All-inclusive: quarterly labs, monthly provider access, protocol management, and 15% off wellness services.</p>
				<a class="wh-text-link sp-packages__link" href="/demos/premium-wellness-clinic/memberships">View Details &rarr;</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<!-- ═══ Related Services — surface bg, row list ═══ -->
<section class="wh-section wh-section--surface sp-related">
	<div class="wh-container">
		<div class="wh-section-header">
			<p class="wh-eyebrow">Related Services</p>
			<h2>Commonly paired with hormone optimization</h2>
		</div>
		<div class="sp-related__list">
			<a class="sp-related__row" href="/demos/premium-wellness-clinic/services">
				<h3>Testosterone Therapy</h3>
				<p>For eligible clients — medically supervised TRT with ongoing monitoring and dose optimization.</p>
				<span class="sp-related__arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span>
			</a>
			<a class="sp-related__row" href="/demos/premium-wellness-clinic/services">
				<h3>Peptide Therapy</h3>
				<p>Targeted peptide protocols for recovery, sleep, body composition, and cellular repair.</p>
				<span class="sp-related__arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span>
			</a>
			<a class="sp-related__row" href="/demos/premium-wellness-clinic/services">
				<h3>Lab Review</h3>
				<p>Standalone comprehensive lab interpretation with provider consult — no protocol required.</p>
				<span class="sp-related__arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span>
			</a>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<!-- ═══ FAQ — split layout ═══ -->
<section class="wh-section sp-faq">
	<div class="wh-container sp-faq__split">
		<div class="sp-faq__left">
			<p class="wh-eyebrow">Questions</p>
			<h2>Hormone Optimization FAQ</h2>
		</div>
		<div class="wh-faq__list">
			<details class="wh-faq__item">
				<summary><span>What hormones are tested?</span></summary>
				<p>Our comprehensive panel typically includes total and free testosterone, estradiol, DHEA-S, thyroid (TSH, free T3, free T4), cortisol, SHBG, progesterone, and metabolic markers like fasting insulin and HbA1c. Your provider may add or adjust based on your specific symptoms.</p>
			</details>
			<details class="wh-faq__item">
				<summary><span>Do I need labs before starting?</span></summary>
				<p>Yes. Lab work is required before any protocol is initiated. We need a clear baseline to make safe, data-driven clinical decisions. If you have recent labs from another provider, we may be able to use those — bring them to your consultation.</p>
			</details>
			<details class="wh-faq__item">
				<summary><span>Does this include testosterone replacement therapy (TRT)?</span></summary>
				<p>It can, for clients who qualify. TRT is one option among many and is only prescribed when labs, symptoms, and health history indicate it is clinically appropriate and safe. Not all clients will qualify or need TRT.</p>
			</details>
			<details class="wh-faq__item">
				<summary><span>Is hormone optimization safe?</span></summary>
				<p>When guided by comprehensive labs and an experienced provider, hormone optimization is considered safe for most adults. Ongoing monitoring is essential. Your provider will discuss risks, benefits, and alternatives specific to your situation during your consultation.</p>
			</details>
			<details class="wh-faq__item">
				<summary><span>How long until I see results?</span></summary>
				<p>Most clients notice initial changes (energy, sleep, mood) within 4–8 weeks. Full optimization often takes 3–6 months of protocol refinement. Hormone optimization is a process, not an overnight fix — patience and consistency matter.</p>
			</details>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<!-- ═══ Final CTA — dark, centered ═══ -->
<section class="wh-section wh-section--dark sp-final">
	<div class="wh-container" style="text-align:center; max-width:640px;">
		<h2>Ready to explore hormone optimization?</h2>
		<p class="wh-lead" style="margin-inline:auto;">Start with a consultation. Your provider will review your symptoms, order labs, and help determine if optimization is right for you.</p>
		<div class="wh-btn-row" style="justify-content:center;">
			<a class="wh-btn wh-btn--primary" href="/demos/premium-wellness-clinic/new-clients">Book a Consultation &rarr;</a>
			<a class="wh-btn wh-btn--secondary" href="/demos/premium-wellness-clinic/new-clients">Ask a Question</a>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

</WellnessLayout>

<style>
/* ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
   SERVICE PAGE — Restrained Clinical Premium
   ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */

/* ─── Hero ─── */
.sp-hero { padding-top: clamp(5rem, 10vw, 9rem); padding-bottom: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 5rem); }
.sp-hero h1 { max-width: none; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
.sp-hero__headline { font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 1rem + 0.5vw, 1.35rem); font-weight: 400; max-width: 620px; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }

/* ─── Quick Facts Strip ─── */
.sp-facts { margin-top: 2.5rem; padding-top: 2rem; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); }
.sp-facts__strip { display: flex; gap: 2.5rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }
.sp-facts__item { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.2rem; }
.sp-facts__label { font-size: 0.6rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.12em; color: var(--wh-sage); }
.sp-facts__value { font-size: 0.88rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--wh-white); }

/* ─── Benefits: numbered list ─── */
.sp-benefits__list { display: flex; flex-direction: column; }
.sp-benefits__item { display: flex; gap: 1rem; padding: 1.15rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--wh-border); }
.sp-benefits__item:first-child { border-top: 1px solid var(--wh-border); }
.sp-benefits__num { font-size: 0.65rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--wh-sage); padding-top: 0.15rem; flex-shrink: 0; min-width: 1.5rem; }
.sp-benefits__item h3 { font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 0.2rem; }
.sp-benefits__item p { font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--wh-muted); }

/* ─── What It Is ─── */
.sp-what__inner { max-width: 680px; }
.sp-what__inner p { font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--wh-text); }

/* ─── Lab Pathway: vertical timeline ─── */
.sp-labpath__timeline { max-width: 600px; margin-top: 2rem; position: relative; }
.sp-labpath__step { display: flex; gap: 1.25rem; position: relative; padding-bottom: 2rem; }
.sp-labpath__step:last-child { padding-bottom: 0; }
.sp-labpath__marker { display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; flex-shrink: 0; position: relative; width: 2rem; }
.sp-labpath__num { font-size: 0.6rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.05em; color: var(--wh-sage); margin-bottom: 0.4rem; }
.sp-labpath__dot { width: 10px; height: 10px; border-radius: 50%; border: 2px solid var(--wh-sage); background: var(--wh-surface); flex-shrink: 0; position: relative; z-index: 1; }
.sp-labpath__step:not(:last-child) .sp-labpath__marker::after { content: ''; position: absolute; top: calc(0.6rem + 0.4rem + 10px); left: 50%; transform: translateX(-50%); width: 1px; height: calc(100% - 0.6rem - 0.4rem - 10px + 2rem); background: var(--wh-border-strong); }
.sp-labpath__body { padding-top: 0.1rem; }
.sp-labpath__body h3 { font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--wh-ink); margin-bottom: 0.2rem; }
.sp-labpath__body p { font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--wh-muted); line-height: 1.6; }
.sp-labpath__note { font-size: 0.78rem; color: var(--wh-muted); margin-top: 2.5rem; max-width: 600px; line-height: 1.6; }

/* ─── Who It's For ─── */
.sp-who__split { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 4rem); }
.sp-who__split > h2 { grid-column: 1 / -1; }
.sp-who__col h3 { font-size: 0.65rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.14em; color: var(--wh-sage); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
.sp-who__col ul { padding-left: 1.1rem; margin: 0; }
.sp-who__col li { font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--wh-muted); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; line-height: 1.55; }
@media (max-width: 520px) { .sp-who__split { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }

/* ─── Process: vertical timeline with dots ─── */
.sp-process__steps { list-style: none; margin: 0; padding: 0; max-width: 560px; }
.sp-process__step { display: flex; gap: 1.5rem; position: relative; padding-bottom: 2.5rem; }
.sp-process__step:last-child { padding-bottom: 0; }
.sp-process__dot { position: relative; width: 10px; flex-shrink: 0; padding-top: 0.35rem; }
.sp-process__dot::before { content: ''; display: block; width: 10px; height: 10px; border-radius: 50%; border: 2px solid var(--wh-sage); background: var(--wh-ink); }
.sp-process__step:not(:last-child) .sp-process__dot::after { content: ''; position: absolute; top: 14px; left: 4.5px; width: 1px; height: calc(100% + 2.5rem - 14px); background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1); }
.sp-process__body h3 { font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--wh-white); margin-bottom: 0.3rem; }
.sp-process__body p { font-size: 0.85rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5); }

/* ─── What to Expect ─── */
.sp-expect__phases { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 2rem; margin-top: 1.5rem; }
.sp-expect__phase h3 { font-size: 0.65rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.14em; color: var(--wh-sage); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
.sp-expect__phase p { font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--wh-muted); line-height: 1.65; }
@media (max-width: 600px) { .sp-expect__phases { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 1.5rem; } }

/* ─── Safety ─── */
.sp-safety__inner { max-width: 680px; }
.sp-safety__inner p { font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.7; }
.sp-safety__inner ul { padding-left: 1.25rem; margin-top: 1rem; }
.sp-safety__inner li { font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--wh-muted); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; line-height: 1.6; }

/* ─── Packages: bordered cards ─── */
.sp-packages__grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 1.25rem; }
